{
  "texts": [
    "Beyond what can be called a word, voices, and sounds enable one to project.",
    "Here, the noise has a distinct rhythm (according to Lefebvre's definition) that makes it possible to preserve a specific time (that of Parker's youth) and space (his school in England), which has theeffect of evoking the feeling of 'turning into a pathetic clown.'",
    "Parkers' Dasein is that of a 'pathetic clown' when faced with the old group of friends.",
    "The distances that he overcomes are not measurable but experiential.",
    "He brings about the others as they are for himself, while simultaneously bringing about the social system 'old friends' group.'"
  ]
}